thread.title: Cowboys LB Sean Lee clears concussion protocol
thread.title_full: Cowboys LB Sean Lee clears concussion protocol - UPI.com

author: upi.com
title: Cowboys LB Sean Lee clears concussion protocol
text:
| License Photo Dallas Cowboys linebacker Sean Lee has cleared the NFL's concussion protocol and is slated to play in Sunday's game against the New England Patriots .
Lee was cleared Thursday and returned to practice. He indicated he had no limitations during practice.
"We're optimistic with how he has responded to everything," Cowboys coach Jason Garrett said.
Lee was injured during Sunday's loss to the New Orleans Saints.
